- 'Blossoms stand tallest' refers to the products with the highest total sales and average ratings;
- 'Crowned by' indicates the products that have achieved both high sales and ratings;
- 'Rank in the marketplace' refers to the ranking of products based on their sales and ratings.

- 'Top 10' refers to the highest total sales value;
- 'Inventory details' include quantity available and reorder level;
- 'Latest sales information' includes the latest sales quantity, price, and date.

- "First five sales" refers to the earliest five sales for each product based on the order date;
- "Total revenue" is the sum of the total prices of the sales;
- "Average revenue per sale" is calculated by dividing the total revenue by the number of sales (up to 5);
- "Average quantity sold" is the average of the quantities sold in the first five sales.

- 'Top 4' refers to the highest-ranking products based on total sales and total views;
- 'Total sales' and 'total views' must be greater than zero;
- 'Average rating' is calculated from user reviews.

- "views" represent the number of times the product page has been viewed;
- "sales" indicate the total number of units sold;
- "average_rating" is the mean rating given by users;
- "clicks" are the number of times the product link was clicked;
- "add_to_cart" is the number of times the product was added to the shopping cart;
- "abandonment_rate" is the rate at which the product was removed from the cart before purchase;
- "conversion_rate" is the rate at which the product was purchased after being added to the cart;
- "total_quantity_sold" and "total_sales_amount" are calculated per category;
- "purchase_count" is the number of unique orders placed by a user;
- "total_spent" is the total amount a user has spent on orders;
- "product_review_average" and "review_count" are based on user reviews.

- 'In Stock' refers to products with a total stock greater than 0;
- 'Out of Stock' refers to products with a total stock of 0;
- 'Average rating' is calculated by averaging the ratings from user reviews.

- High engagement score indicates a product that is frequently viewed and successfully converted into sales;
- Conversion rate is the percentage of users who view the product and ultimately make a purchase;
- The query focuses on products with more than 500 views to ensure a sufficient sample size for meaningful engagement metrics.

- 'More popular product categories' refers to categories with 10 or more products;
- 'Total sales' and 'average ratings' are calculated for each category;
- The results are ordered by total sales in descending order.

- 'Shipped' status indicates the order has left the warehouse and is on its way to the customer;
- 'Total sales' is the sum of the total price for all shipped orders of a product;
- 'Average rating' is the mean rating given by users who have reviewed the product.

- The "first half of 2023" refers to the period from January 1, 2023, to June 30, 2023;
- "Spent the most" implies the highest total spending on orders;
- "Average product rating" is the mean rating of the products ordered by each user.

- "frequent buyers" refers to users who have placed more than one order;
- "popular products" are those with higher total orders and quantities sold;
- The time period "first half of 2023" refers to January 1, 2023, to June 30, 2023.

- 'Defiance X12' is a specific product in the database;
- 'Average rating' is calculated from user reviews;
- 'Total sold' refers to the total quantity of the product that has been ordered.

- 'Popular product' refers to the product with the highest views and sales;
- 'Engaged with' includes viewing and purchasing the product;
- 'Product's performance metrics' include views, sales, average rating, and conversion rate.

- 'High average rating' refers to an average rating greater than 4.0;
- 'Significant stock' implies a higher quantity available in the inventory;
- 'Specified category' refers to the category with ID 0.

- "blossoms have garnered the most admiration and praise" refers to products with high sales and high ratings;
- "widely sold" refers to the total quantity sold;
- "received the highest average ratings" refers to the average rating from user reviews;
- "views attracted" refers to the number of views the product has received.

- "Top-selling products" refers to the products with the highest total sales;
- "Performance" includes metrics such as ratings, stock, and revenue;
- "Category's average ratings" is the average rating of all products within the same category;
- "Total category stock" is the total stock available for all products within the same category.

- 'Best-selling products' refers to products with the highest total sales;
- 'User interaction metrics' include total views, total clicks, total add-to-cart actions, total abandonment rate, and total conversion rate;
- 'Stock availability' refers to the total quantity available in stock.
